Documented Information is a mandatory requirement (clause 7.5), pursuant to ISO Annex SL, which defines the mandatory construct of an ISO management system. Documented Information includes all forms and manner of official communications subject to management, protection, and used as necessary to establish traceability and auditable evidence to demonstrate adherence to ISO management standards.
